  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and dice half your<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>brown onion[s] </strong>as finely as you can</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems and chop both the <strong>mint</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> roughly</p><p>Combine your<strong> lamb mince </strong>in a large bowl with the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>half </strong>of the<strong> chopped coriander</strong> and <strong>mint </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a<strong> </strong>generous pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, then<strong> </strong>set aside – this is your <strong>seekh kebab mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632472062463-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632472062463-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632472062463-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632472062463-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1632472062463-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>remaining brown onions</strong></p><p>Line a baking tray with<strong> non-stick baking paper</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sliced onions</strong>, 1/3 of your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>garam masala </strong>and <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a separate large bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>gram flour</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong> and massage for 30 secs adding an extra splash of water if its looking a bit dry</p><p>Scoop out 2 handfuls of the mixture per person, shape into rough bhaji shapes and add to the tray (or two!)</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>onion bhajis</strong> with a little <strong>vegetable oil </strong>then put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632472352785-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632472352785-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632472352785-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632472352785-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1632472352785-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the bhajis are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chicken </strong>to a bowl with 1/3 of the <strong>ground</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>turmeric </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> of <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>,<strong> </strong>mix up<strong> </strong>and set aside to marinate (save the rest of the yoghurt for later!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632472356928-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632472356928-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632472356928-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632472356928-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1632472356928-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low, sprinkle over the <strong>remaining ground turmeric</strong> and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>turmeric rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632472362308-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632472362308-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632472362308-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632472362308-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1632472362308-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the<strong> remaining ginger & garlic paste </strong>and <strong>remaining garam masala </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of vegetable oil if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and stir in your <strong>tomato paste</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>to the pan with the onions and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until thickened slightly – this is your<strong> curry base</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632472369934-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632472369934-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632472369934-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632472369934-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1632472369934-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the bhajis are golden and crispy, move the tray[s] to the bottom of the oven to keep warm, then preheat the grill to medium-high</p><p>Divide the <strong>seekh kebab mixture</strong>  and roll into 2 sausage shapes per person</p><p>Tip: Wet your hands to stop the mince sticking to them!</p><p>Lightly oil a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and add the <strong>seekh kebabs </strong>and <strong>sweet pointed pepper[s] </strong>(no need to chop!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] under the grill for 12-15 min, turning everything halfway, or until the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) and everything is starting to char</p><p>Once cooked, carefully slice your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> in half widthways</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632472374999-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632472374999-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632472374999-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632472374999-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1632472374999-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the curry base has thickened slightly, add the <strong>marinated chicken</strong> to the pan, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min further or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>While the chicken is cooking, combine <strong>half</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>your <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>with the<strong> remaining chopped mint </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>mint raita</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>garlic &</strong> <strong>coriander naan[s]</strong> to a toaster for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632472379466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632472379466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632472379466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632472379466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1632472379466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, remove the pan from the heat and stir in the<strong> remaining natural yoghurt</strong> – this is your <strong>butter chicken</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>butter chicken</strong>,<strong> lamb seekh kebabs</strong>,<strong> pepper halves </strong>and <strong>onion bhajis </strong>with the <strong>mint raita</strong>, <strong>turmeric rice </strong>and <strong>toasted naans</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish the lamb seekh kebabs with the <strong>remaining chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
